Motorists in the country could possibly have to dig even deeper in their pockets amid an expected fuel increase next month. The price of petrol is said to likely increase to R24 a litre. The pressure lies on the government to try to mitigate this. Avhapfani Tshifularo, from the South African Petroleum Industry Association unpacks the implications of the increase. #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Motorists should be bracing themselves for a fuel price hike in April. Petrol is expected to cost about R2 a litre more and the diesel price to rise by R3 a litre. READ: Record fuel price increase predicted The ongoing conflict between Ukraine and Russia is blamed for the possible increase. Government is now under pressure to try and mitigate this. However, the South African Petroleum Industry Association says it is a tough challenge. Watch the video above for more details on this story. 